# Staying Calm Before Your Job Interview

Here are some strategies to help you manage your nerves on interview morning:

## Preparation (Evening Before)
- Lay out your clothes and materials the night before
- Get a good night's sleep (7-8 hours ideally)
- Review your notes once, then set them aside

## Morning Routine
- Give yourself extra time to get ready and commute
- Eat a light, nutritious breakfast
- Limit caffeine if it increases your anxiety
- Practice deep breathing: 4 counts in, hold for 4, 4 counts out
- Take a short walk if possible to release nervous energy

## Mental Strategies
- Remind yourself that nervousness means you care - it's normal
- Visualize the interview going well for 5 minutes
- Use positive self-talk: "I am prepared" or "I have valuable skills to offer"
- Remember that an interview is a two-way conversation, not just an evaluation

If nerves hit right before the interview, try the 5-5-5 technique: name 5 things you can see, 5 things you can hear, and 5 things you can feel.

